<br>
1. TAB 1 loads and populates the session varaibles.<br>
2. TAB 2 you make changes you want reflected in TAB 1<br>
<br>
HOW TO:<br>
<br>
To dynamically change the values in TAB 1 from TAB 2  you need to refresh the TAB 1 page when you click on a SAVE on TAB 2.<br>
<br>
If you don't have a SAVE BUTTON you can use the ONCLICK event in the form object that changes the session variables (possibly a submit button) on TAB 2 to auto-refresh TAB 1<br>
<br>
Here is the javascript to refresh TAB 1 from TAB 2:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
&lt;script&gt;
function refreshTAB()
{
document.parent.iframe0.location = 'url to refresh';
}
&lt;/script&gt;
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
To use the FORM tag to trigger the refresh:<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
In the FORM statement of TAB 2 add the ONSUBMIT event statement:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
&lt;F0RM ONSUBMIT=&quot;refreshTAB()&quot;&gt;
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
To use the ONCLICK or ONCHANGE event to trigger the refresh ADD THE ONCLICK or ONCHANGE event to any input field that you want to trigger the refresh:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
&lt;INPUT ... ONCHANGE = &quot;resfreshTAB()&quot;&gt;
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
Please note:<br>
Each tab can be ID'd by the following:<br>
TAB 1 is lFRAME0, TAB 2 is lFRAME1 etc.<br>
